%N A274821 Hexagonal spiral constructed on the nodes of the infinite triangular net in which each term is the least positive integer such that no diagonal contains a repeated term.
%C A274821 Also spiral constructed on the infinite hexagonal grid in which each term is the least positive integer such that no diagonal of successive adjacent cells contains a repeated term. Every number is located in the center of a hexagonal cell. Every cell is also the center of three diagonals of successive adjacent cells.
